  <front>
   <head>To Mrs. —</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">, when you oblige again.</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Subdue that haughty Eye:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Rather than Insolence sustain,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Who would not wish to die?</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A grateful Heart will own the Debt,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But, O! must feel it with Regret.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
